{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 01:08:00.576823", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary of Network Health\n- Underlay routing: Healthy. OSPF adjacencies and routes are present and stable across the core, distribution, and server-access layers.\n  - server_access_router has 10.200.0.0/24 directly connected and OSPF routes to all user subnets.\n  - router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1 have OSPF routes to 10.200.0.0/24 via the core.\n- IP reachability: Normal. End hosts can ping the server farm (DNS, LB, and web servers) with low RTT and no loss.\n  - Examples from host_1_1_1_1 and host_2_1_1_1 show successful pings to 10.200.0.2 (DNS), 10.200.0.7 (LB), 10.200.0.3/0.4 (web servers).\n- HTTP by IP: Normal. Curl tests to http://10.200.0.7 (LB) and http://10.200.0.3 (web_server_0) succeed with reasonable TTFB and total times (~1–2.3 s).\n- Backend isolation: Enforced as designed. Attempts to reach backend_web_0 are unroutable (Destination Net Unreachable to 20.200.0.2), indicating backends are not exposed to user segments, as intended.\n\nDetected Anomaly\n- DNS name resolution failure across the network:\n  - Curl to http://web99.local and http://web0.local from multiple hosts consistently returns total ≈ 5.0 s with zeroed timing fields, indicating DNS resolution timeout (no name lookup/connect happened).\n  - Direct DNS queries time out: dig @10.200.0.2 web0.local and dig @10.200.0.2 web99.local fail from hosts with timeouts.\n  - Even on the DNS server itself, dig @127.0.0.1 web0.local times out.\n\nFault Localization\n- Faulty device: dns_server (10.200.0.2).\n  - Host resolv.conf on clients points to 10.200.0.2 (correct).\n  - dns_server ports appear present in netstat/ss, but DNS queries (UDP/TCP 53) do not get responses (timeouts from both remote hosts and locally on dns_server).\n  - Systemd state on dns_server: bind9.service is inactive (dead).\n  - No named/bind process found (ps output indicates no running DNS daemon).\n  - No firewall blocking observed (iptables policies are ACCEPT).\n\nRoot Cause\n- The authoritative DNS service (BIND) on dns_server is not running. With bind9.service inactive (dead), the server does not respond to UDP/TCP 53 queries, resulting in DNS timeouts for all clients.\n  - Configuration files indicate the correct local zone setup:\n    - /etc/bind/named.conf references zone \"local\" with file /etc/bind/db.local.\n    - /etc/bind/db.local contains A records for web0–web3 and web99 pointing to 10.200.0.3–.7.\n    - recursion no; is appropriate for an authoritative-only local zone but is moot because the process is not running.\n- This is not a routing or reachability problem (ping to 10.200.0.2 is fine; OSPF routes are correct), nor a firewall issue. The failure is service-level on dns_server.\n\nImpact\n- All hostname-based access to local services (e.g., web0.local, web99.local) fails due to DNS timeouts, despite IP-layer connectivity and server health being normal.\n- Users can reach services by IP but not by their configured local DNS names.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 44029, "output_tokens": 3361, "total_tokens": 47390, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 42368}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2560}}}
